1
01:33:40,717 --> 01:33:44,073
Who did you bring home last year?
Sheila...?

2
01:33:44,237 --> 01:33:48,674
- I didn't go home last year.
- What about the year before?

3
01:33:48,837 --> 01:33:52,796
I'm not the first girl
you ever brought home, right?

4
01:33:53,597 --> 01:33:57,385
Jackson! Oh, God!

5
01:33:57,557 --> 01:33:59,866
Oh, no!

6
01:34:00,037 --> 01:34:02,756
This makes it worse.

7
01:34:32,357 --> 01:34:35,747
You never told me it was like this.

8
01:34:35,917 --> 01:34:42,914
It's a farm. There's a mortgage.
It's no big deal.

9
01:34:43,077 --> 01:34:45,386
My God!

10
01:34:49,717 --> 01:34:54,916
- Some farmhouse you've got here.
- Watch your step on the ice.

11
01:35:16,837 --> 01:35:20,386
Come along. Don't be impressed.

12
01:35:25,917 --> 01:35:30,195
- Hush, you'll wake her up.
- I'm sorry.

13
01:35:31,397 --> 01:35:34,912
- She's put you in the guest room.
- Bummer.

14
01:35:35,077 --> 01:35:38,547
- Where are you?
- Across the hall.

15
01:35:40,037 --> 01:35:43,712
- Well, it's her house.
- It's a Catholic thing.

16
01:35:44,997 --> 01:35:48,194
- Come on.
- No way.

17
01:35:48,357 --> 01:35:53,067
I'll sneak you back
before she knows.

18
01:36:11,677 --> 01:36:16,512
An angel in the kitchen
and a devil in the bedroom...

19
01:36:16,677 --> 01:36:20,226
Now that's what I like in a man.

20
01:36:20,997 --> 01:36:25,195
Oh, my God!

21
01:36:25,357 --> 01:36:30,226
I am sorry. I thought you were
in the other room.

22
01:36:30,397 --> 01:36:36,188
I am. I just came in here
this morning... to say hello.

23
01:36:36,357 --> 01:36:40,873
I guess I'd better hurry up
and be embarrassed.

24
01:36:41,037 --> 01:36:44,871
- I thought you were Jackson.
- Yes, I could tell.

25
01:36:46,397 --> 01:36:50,675
- Please forgive me.
- No, I just...

26
01:36:50,837 --> 01:36:54,273
- Well, hi, I'm Helen.
- Of course you are.

27
01:36:54,437 --> 01:36:58,874
I'm Martha Baring.
Welcome to Kilronan.

28
01:36:59,037 --> 01:37:05,146
- Thank you. Oh, boy!
- Where is that son of mine?

29
01:37:05,317 --> 01:37:09,196
I don't know,
but I'd like to find him.

30
01:37:09,357 --> 01:37:11,825
So would I.

31
01:37:13,837 --> 01:37:17,796
So much for first impressions.
You enjoy his breakfast.

32
01:37:17,957 --> 01:37:21,586
I look forward to seeing
a lot less of you downstairs.

33
01:37:21,757 --> 01:37:25,306
Oh, my God!

34
01:37:32,157 --> 01:37:36,992
You show a lot of promise
for a city girl.

35
01:37:37,157 --> 01:37:41,673
- Thank you. You're a terrific liar.
- Well...!

36
01:37:41,837 --> 01:37:46,353
- Mom, the place looks great.
- Only when it's covered with snow.

37
01:37:46,517 --> 01:37:50,635
It's been hard this fall,
but that's too depressing.

38
01:37:50,797 --> 01:37:54,915
Let talk about our week. I made
some plans. I hope you don't mind.

39
01:37:55,077 --> 01:37:58,433
- We can't stay the week.
- Of course you can.

40
01:37:58,597 --> 01:38:02,829
We have to leave
right after Christmas. I'm sorry.

41
01:38:04,197 --> 01:38:08,031
- Darling...!
- We have to leave on Wednesday.

42
01:38:10,397 --> 01:38:15,073
Of course, if you have to leave.
I just thought maybe...

43
01:38:15,237 --> 01:38:18,707
Well, never mind.

44
01:38:18,877 --> 01:38:23,393
Look at the time.
We have to get back for church.

45
01:38:28,157 --> 01:38:32,833
- Go on. Go after her.
- She misses me.

46
01:38:32,997 --> 01:38:35,716
Go.

47
01:38:41,317 --> 01:38:46,550
I made a better impression
with my clothes <i>off</i>.

48
01:38:46,717 --> 01:38:51,393
You look great. You look beautiful.

49
01:38:51,557 --> 01:38:57,871
I love this house, Jackson.
There's something about it.

50
01:38:58,037 --> 01:39:00,597
- I suppose.
- Maybe it's you.

51
01:39:00,757 --> 01:39:06,673
- How me?
- Where you're from. Who you are.

52
01:39:06,837 --> 01:39:10,147
The architecture of a life.

53
01:39:11,517 --> 01:39:15,396
- Pretentious?
- Just a little.

54
01:39:17,397 --> 01:39:21,026
What?

55
01:39:39,717 --> 01:39:43,392
Look at you.
You're putting me to shame.

56
01:39:43,557 --> 01:39:46,913
Do you think
this is too much for church?

57
01:39:47,077 --> 01:39:50,990
No, not at all.
I envy your confidence.

58
01:39:52,397 --> 01:39:56,709
Are you sure?
I did bring another one.

59
01:39:56,877 --> 01:40:02,634
I'm just worried you'll get cold
in that freezing old church. Here.

60
01:40:04,517 --> 01:40:09,272
- Oh, it's broken.
- It's just an old catch.

61
01:40:10,597 --> 01:40:13,987
I'll have it fixed.

62
01:40:14,157 --> 01:40:19,311
- Are these your parents?
- Yes.

63
01:40:19,477 --> 01:40:26,189
- And where are they this Christmas?
- They died... a long time ago.

64
01:40:26,357 --> 01:40:30,145
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

65
01:40:31,837 --> 01:40:35,989
Okay, you can stop talking about me.

66
01:40:38,357 --> 01:40:40,666
Let's go.

67
01:40:40,837 --> 01:40:43,397
Go ahead... Please, go on.

68
01:40:43,557 --> 01:40:46,629
I love the scarf.

69
01:40:47,677 --> 01:40:52,956
"And the angel came to her and said:
The Lord is with thee."

70
01:40:53,117 --> 01:40:56,348
"And you will conceive in your womb
and bear a son."

71
01:40:56,517 --> 01:41:01,875
"The Lord God will give him
the throne of his father David."

72
01:41:02,037 --> 01:41:04,676
"His kingdom shall be without end."

73
01:41:04,837 --> 01:41:07,954
Amen.

74
01:41:12,997 --> 01:41:18,913
- Hello, Father.
- Jackson, the prodigal returns.

75
01:41:19,077 --> 01:41:24,629
Baring and Son, back in business.
You've made your mother very happy.

76
01:41:24,797 --> 01:41:28,836
I've been happy
since the day he was born.

77
01:41:31,677 --> 01:41:36,910
Does everyone think I'm moving in,
or is Madge just a trial balloon?

78
01:41:37,077 --> 01:41:40,035
I put an ad in the paper.

79
01:41:40,197 --> 01:41:44,429
I didn't,
but I guess my hopes were showing.

80
01:41:44,597 --> 01:41:48,590
You want me to work this place,
but my job's in New York.

81
01:41:48,757 --> 01:41:53,194
- You don't love that job.
- Helen's in New York.

82
01:41:53,357 --> 01:41:55,871
That's mighty inconsiderate of you.

83
01:41:56,037 --> 01:42:02,670
Steal away my baby boy.
Why can't you just be sensible?

84
01:42:02,837 --> 01:42:05,874
Leave your life, your work,
your friends, -

85
01:42:06,037 --> 01:42:09,109
- and move in
with a controlling old woman.

86
01:42:09,277 --> 01:42:16,672
- Bake bread and shovel horse shit.
- You're not that old.

87
01:42:16,837 --> 01:42:21,865
I'm sorry, sweetheart.
Don't let Madge spoil our Christmas.

88
01:42:23,117 --> 01:42:26,951
- Good night.
- Good night.

89
01:42:53,437 --> 01:42:56,429
Martha.

90
01:43:17,237 --> 01:43:20,354
Hello.

91
01:43:20,517 --> 01:43:26,274
I'm sorry to disturb you. I'm lost.
I'm looking for Kilronan.

92
01:43:26,437 --> 01:43:29,793
Back thataways.
The tar road.

93
01:43:29,957 --> 01:43:34,473
- Second on the left.
- Okay, thank you.

94
01:43:34,637 --> 01:43:40,234
Tell Mrs. Baring
I'll bring the birds by later on.

95
01:43:40,397 --> 01:43:42,627
Merry Christmas.

96
01:43:45,477 --> 01:43:52,155
- Where've you been?
- I'll tell you about it later.

97
01:43:52,317 --> 01:43:58,153
- You cleaned up? I'm shocked.
- It must have been my mother.

98
01:44:00,517 --> 01:44:03,236
She does all this with no help?

99
01:44:03,397 --> 01:44:07,515
The help never stays. She doesn't
give them anything to do.

100
01:44:07,677 --> 01:44:11,226
I caved in.
We're staying for New Year's Eve.

101
01:44:11,397 --> 01:44:14,514
Ten, nine, eight, seven, -

102
01:44:14,677 --> 01:44:17,635
- six, five, four, three, -

103
01:44:17,797 --> 01:44:21,915
- two, one... Happy New Year!

104
01:44:22,077 --> 01:44:24,352
Happy New Year.

105
01:44:27,357 --> 01:44:31,270
- Still love me?
- I'll love you, dear.

106
01:44:31,437 --> 01:44:34,713
I'll love you
till China and Africa meet...

107
01:44:34,877 --> 01:44:39,951
...and the river jumps over
the mountains.

108
01:44:59,557 --> 01:45:03,106
- Did you have a good time?
- It was a great party.

109
01:45:03,277 --> 01:45:08,192
I'd say it was a triumph.
Short-lived maybe... never mind.

110
01:45:08,357 --> 01:45:13,636
- Here's to you, my darlings.
- Good night.

111
01:45:29,397 --> 01:45:33,549
- Happy New Year.
- Happy New Year.

112
01:45:43,717 --> 01:45:46,629
Oh, my God! Jackson!

113
01:45:46,797 --> 01:45:51,587
You're right, you do make a better
impression with your clothes off.

114
01:46:28,917 --> 01:46:33,388
- All ready?
- I think so.

115
01:46:33,557 --> 01:46:39,109
I almost forgot.
I had it fixed.

116
01:46:40,477 --> 01:46:44,356
You shouldn't have.

117
01:46:45,357 --> 01:46:49,748
- It's perfect.
- Well...

118
01:46:56,397 --> 01:47:03,075
- Now I've gone and set you off.
- I'm not so good with goodbyes.

119
01:47:04,837 --> 01:47:07,954
Well, you just go on then.

120
01:47:08,517 --> 01:47:12,066
Bye, Mom.

121
01:47:15,077 --> 01:47:19,389
Bye, baby. You take care out there.

122
01:48:00,557 --> 01:48:03,754
Last flight.

123
01:48:06,237 --> 01:48:10,992
- I know, I haven't fixed it yet.
- You are so punished.

124
01:48:11,157 --> 01:48:14,991
- No sex.
- Not again.

125
01:48:15,157 --> 01:48:19,275
Oh well, be it ever so humble...

126
01:48:19,437 --> 01:48:22,235
Home, sweet home.

127
01:48:24,557 --> 01:48:29,073
- How was the vacation?
- His mom was great. He was weird.

128
01:48:29,237 --> 01:48:31,592
It's being around their mothers.

129
01:48:31,757 --> 01:48:35,352
It's all about the breasts.

130
01:48:35,517 --> 01:48:39,396
Men are always talking to their
shrinks about their mothers.

131
01:48:39,557 --> 01:48:45,871
And women always talking to their
shrinks about their mothers-in-law.

132
01:48:46,037 --> 01:48:49,586
Like mine.
I'm not joking. You'll see.

133
01:48:49,757 --> 01:48:54,353
Wait, you marry the guy.
The mother is his problem.

134
01:48:54,517 --> 01:48:59,033
We've projected to complete
that phase within 16 months.

135
01:48:59,197 --> 01:49:04,317
This new triple-E glass
is non-reflective -

136
01:49:04,477 --> 01:49:10,632
- minimalizing visual impact,
optimalizing, if that's a word -

137
01:49:10,797 --> 01:49:16,190
- energy conservation
for both heating... and cooling.

138
01:49:18,237 --> 01:49:21,786
The 60% glass...

139
01:49:49,517 --> 01:49:52,987
You're home early. Are you okay?

140
01:49:54,077 --> 01:49:57,786
- I don't know.
- What do you mean?

141
01:49:58,717 --> 01:50:00,628
I'm pregnant.

142
01:50:05,717 --> 01:50:11,269
This is where you're supposed to go,
"Are you sure?"

143
01:50:11,437 --> 01:50:16,306
It seems my diaphragm is broken.

144
01:50:18,757 --> 01:50:24,150
- Marry me.
- Oh, Jackson...

145
01:50:24,317 --> 01:50:28,356
I think I lost my job today, too.
I barfed on Gavin.

146
01:50:31,557 --> 01:50:36,790
You said you wouldn't get married
unless you were pregnant.

147
01:50:36,957 --> 01:50:39,994
You're pregnant. It's settled.

148
01:50:41,677 --> 01:50:44,749
I love you.

149
01:50:45,637 --> 01:50:48,231
Marry me.

150
01:50:51,677 --> 01:50:53,986
Is that a yes?

151
01:51:10,717 --> 01:51:15,188
- <i>Are you sitting down?</i>
- Don't tell her I'm pregnant.

152
01:51:15,357 --> 01:51:19,191
- <i>What is it? Tell me.</i>
- Helen and I are getting married.

153
01:51:20,837 --> 01:51:24,876
- She's pregnant, isn't she?
- How did you guess?

154
01:51:27,757 --> 01:51:32,194
Mothers know these things.
Where is she? Is she there?

155
01:51:32,357 --> 01:51:38,034
- Hi, Martha.
- <i>Isn't this the best news ever?</i>

156
01:51:38,197 --> 01:51:42,907
A baby...
and a wedding, too, I suppose.

157
01:51:43,077 --> 01:51:46,387
When will it be?
We'd better hurry, hadn't we?

158
01:51:46,557 --> 01:51:49,469
<i>We could have it here at Kilronan.</i>

159
01:51:49,637 --> 01:51:55,189
- We were thinking of City Hall.
- We were?

160
01:51:56,677 --> 01:52:01,512
May the Lord bless these rings
as a sign of your fidelity and love.

161
01:52:01,677 --> 01:52:05,511
What God hath joined together
let no man put asunder.

162
01:52:05,677 --> 01:52:09,750
By the power vested in me
I now pronounce you man and wife.

163
01:52:09,917 --> 01:52:12,875
You may kiss the bride.

164
01:52:20,837 --> 01:52:23,590
- You look lovely.
- Good luck, Helen.

165
01:52:23,757 --> 01:52:28,353
- Hi, congratulations.
- Thanks.

166
01:52:29,277 --> 01:52:30,869
Hi.

167
01:52:31,037 --> 01:52:35,394
Hey, how are you holding up?

168
01:52:37,357 --> 01:52:41,873
- I'm dying.
- So Helen...

169
01:52:42,037 --> 01:52:45,074
- Who's that?
- I don't know.

170
01:52:47,197 --> 01:52:50,155
- What?
- She got him back.

171
01:52:50,317 --> 01:52:53,707
- Who?
- Your new mother-in-law.

172
01:52:53,877 --> 01:52:57,552
- You never showed for lunch.
- Were we supposed to?

173
01:52:57,717 --> 01:53:01,756
You could come visit me
at the home for the near dead.

174
01:53:01,917 --> 01:53:05,671
Your mother-in-law said
you had bigger fish to fry.

175
01:53:07,277 --> 01:53:09,996
Alice Baring.
I'm Jackson's grandmother.

176
01:53:10,157 --> 01:53:15,470
I'm sorry. Hello, she never told me
we were supposed to have lunch.

177
01:53:15,637 --> 01:53:19,630
She wouldn't.
You have to be so careful of Martha.

178
01:53:19,797 --> 01:53:26,873
That's why I invited myself. I'm the
only one left on his father's side.

179
01:53:27,037 --> 01:53:30,234
Let's see the handcuff?

180
01:53:30,397 --> 01:53:36,393
- It looks familiar.
- It belonged to Jackson's mother.

181
01:53:36,557 --> 01:53:40,596
I gave it to her...
that was before I knew her better.

182
01:53:40,757 --> 01:53:44,750
- When are you due?
- How did you know that?

183
01:53:44,917 --> 01:53:51,231
You can't be stupid breeding horses.
It takes knowhow and control.

184
01:53:51,397 --> 01:53:54,514
One man to help the stallion.
One to help the mare.

185
01:53:54,677 --> 01:53:58,272
One to hold the tail,
and one to finesse the situation.

186
01:53:59,277 --> 01:54:03,953
Now Martha, she can manage
all that by herself.

187
01:54:04,117 --> 01:54:07,996
Alice! What a surprise!
I didn't think you could make it.

188
01:54:08,157 --> 01:54:14,073
Yes, wasn't it lucky?
I just followed the catering trucks.

189
01:54:14,237 --> 01:54:20,153
Why don't you come with me?
They want a picture of you two.

190
01:54:22,557 --> 01:54:26,152
- Take your damn hands off me.
- Oh, Alice.

191
01:55:37,357 --> 01:55:40,793
One word
and I'll slice you wide open.

192
01:55:40,957 --> 01:55:45,394
- You got that, pretty lady?
- Please, don't hurt me.

193
01:55:47,277 --> 01:55:53,466
- My very pretty lady.
- Please, I'm pregnant.

194
01:55:59,837 --> 01:56:05,355
I know where you live.
Don't you forget that.

195
01:56:35,597 --> 01:56:38,236
Very close call.

196
01:56:38,397 --> 01:56:44,233
- You told him you were pregnant?
- Most men run when they hear that.

197
01:56:44,397 --> 01:56:47,992
Bad joke. I'm sorry.

198
01:56:48,157 --> 01:56:53,231
- You take care and get some rest.
- Okay.

199
01:56:58,477 --> 01:57:03,028
I can't get his voice
out of my head.

200
01:57:32,637 --> 01:57:37,153
- My God! I can't go!
- Look...

201
01:57:39,557 --> 01:57:44,312
And I changed the locks.

202
01:57:53,917 --> 01:58:01,505
Are you okay? You sure?
You're going to be all right.

203
01:58:01,677 --> 01:58:03,429
Surprise!

204
01:58:06,557 --> 01:58:10,709
Honey, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to frighten you.

205
01:58:10,877 --> 01:58:14,392
- How did you get in here?
- The super let me in.

206
01:58:14,557 --> 01:58:19,995
Hello, darling.
Hi, good to see you.

207
01:58:21,877 --> 01:58:24,835
You're sure you're all right?

208
01:58:26,437 --> 01:58:30,396
- He took my locket.
- Oh, no!

209
01:58:30,557 --> 01:58:37,713
With the picture of your parents?
Darling, I'm so sorry.

210
01:58:41,997 --> 01:58:45,672
The land alone
is worth more than this.

211
01:58:45,837 --> 01:58:50,228
It's a developer.
You know, golf course and houses.

212
01:58:50,397 --> 01:58:55,073
They'll have to tear out
all the barns, the paddocks.

213
01:58:55,237 --> 01:58:58,946
Turn the pastures into fairways.

214
01:58:59,117 --> 01:59:03,315
Kilronan...
Country Club and Estates.

215
01:59:03,477 --> 01:59:06,708
Can you imagine?

216
01:59:06,877 --> 01:59:10,347
Two years ago we were offered
three times this much.

217
01:59:10,517 --> 01:59:15,147
Then, it was a going concern.
The oldest horse farm in the county.

218
01:59:17,997 --> 01:59:23,629
- Where are you going to go?
- I don't know.

219
01:59:23,797 --> 01:59:26,391
I've never been anywhere else.

220
01:59:28,837 --> 01:59:38,030
Look, Jackson... I can't run
that place all by myself any more.

221
01:59:38,197 --> 01:59:41,746
And if you can't help...

222
01:59:41,917 --> 01:59:47,037
...then you've
got to let me sell it.

223
01:59:47,197 --> 01:59:50,394
I'm going to get the coffee.

224
01:59:54,237 --> 02:00:01,029
- Does she need your permission?
- It's mine, all of it.

225
02:00:01,197 --> 02:00:05,076
It was left to me, not to Martha.

226
02:00:14,237 --> 02:00:18,753
How long do you think it would take
to fix up Kilronan?

227
02:00:18,917 --> 02:00:25,834
Renovate the stables, the stock
is down to nothing... maybe a year.

228
02:00:25,997 --> 02:00:30,548
- Make it attractive to a buyer?
- I'll run some projections.

229
02:00:30,717 --> 02:00:35,552
- Why don't we do it?
- I will, in the morning.

230
02:00:35,717 --> 02:00:40,871
No, I mean
why don't we do the whole thing?

231
02:00:41,037 --> 02:00:44,427
What do you mean?

232
02:00:44,597 --> 02:00:47,589
This could be a great opportunity.

233
02:00:47,757 --> 02:00:52,273
You could do the horses
and I could do the house.

234
02:00:52,437 --> 02:00:55,190
There's two mortgages.

235
02:00:55,357 --> 02:00:59,953
They'd fall all over themselves
to loan you money.

236
02:01:00,117 --> 02:01:06,556
- What do you think?
- I don't know.

237
02:01:06,717 --> 02:01:10,073
I just don't know.

238
02:01:14,397 --> 02:01:18,356
Maybe we'll fall in love
with the place and want to stay?

239
02:01:18,517 --> 02:01:23,637
- What about my mom?
- What about her? I like her.

240
02:01:23,797 --> 02:01:29,269
- What about the baby?
- My God! What was I thinking?

241
02:01:29,437 --> 02:01:33,316
Deprive my child
of the wholesome family values -

242
02:01:33,477 --> 02:01:36,150
- of a New York City childhood.

243
02:01:36,317 --> 02:01:40,515
The dirt, the noise.
Who could want more?

244
02:01:40,677 --> 02:01:45,034
Let's talk.
I need to tell you something.

245
02:01:48,317 --> 02:01:55,268
You know my father died. What you
don't know... is it was my fault.

246
02:01:55,437 --> 02:02:03,310
When he fell?
Honey, you were seven years old.

247
02:02:03,477 --> 02:02:10,394
I was hiding under the stairs.
My parents were arguing.

248
02:02:10,557 --> 02:02:13,629
There was this woman,
Robin Hayes.

249
02:02:13,797 --> 02:02:17,153
My father was leaving us
to be with her.

250
02:02:17,317 --> 02:02:20,593
My mom stormed out
and my father went after her.

251
02:02:20,757 --> 02:02:23,590
I charged in to save her.

252
02:02:26,997 --> 02:02:30,876
I went straight into him.

253
02:02:31,037 --> 02:02:33,995
He stumbled back
and lost his balance.

254
02:02:34,157 --> 02:02:37,672
The doors were open
to the basement stairs...

255
02:02:40,077 --> 02:02:43,194
...and he went down.

256
02:02:44,637 --> 02:02:51,076
I was screaming. It seemed like
forever before my mom heard me.

257
02:02:51,237 --> 02:02:56,789
She'd been pulling the boards off
the old shed I had for my kittens.

258
02:02:56,957 --> 02:03:00,632
She came in.
She had this look on her face.

259
02:03:00,797 --> 02:03:08,385
She was still holding
the nail puller and the tool basket.

260
02:03:08,557 --> 02:03:13,267
She dropped them
and they made this loud sound.

261
02:03:14,157 --> 02:03:20,187
Then she... hugged me tight.

262
02:03:21,797 --> 02:03:25,028
And said it was just an accident.

263
02:03:25,717 --> 02:03:28,675
She did.

264
02:03:29,757 --> 02:03:31,793
Baby...

265
02:03:33,397 --> 02:03:37,595
I hated him for the affair.

266
02:03:37,757 --> 02:03:40,988
The way he hurt her.

267
02:03:43,877 --> 02:03:46,596
But I still...

268
02:03:46,757 --> 02:03:48,873
...love him.

269
02:03:53,917 --> 02:03:59,310
You've been living with these ghosts
for so long. You should go home.

270
02:03:59,477 --> 02:04:03,629
We should. Face all those ghosts.

271
02:04:03,797 --> 02:04:07,836
Live in the home that you loved.
With your mother...

272
02:04:07,997 --> 02:04:11,228
...and me... and our daughter.

273
02:04:12,317 --> 02:04:16,868
And our daughter? Is there
something you're not telling me?

274
02:04:17,037 --> 02:04:21,155
I guess my hopes are showing.
It runs in the family.

275
02:04:30,557 --> 02:04:34,186
- Congratulations, Mr. Baring.
- You've done it.

276
02:05:08,237 --> 02:05:13,470
Dear God, thank you
for bringing my family home at last.

277
02:05:25,477 --> 02:05:28,992
- What happened to you?
- Don't ask.

278
02:05:32,837 --> 02:05:36,546
- Here.
- Oh, God.

279
02:05:37,157 --> 02:05:40,354
How do you really think
Helen is doing?

280
02:05:40,517 --> 02:05:45,068
- What do you mean?
- She just seems so...

281
02:05:45,237 --> 02:05:49,116
...delicate and fragile.
I worry about her.

282
02:05:50,597 --> 02:05:53,794
Every woman is different, but...

283
02:05:54,397 --> 02:05:57,389
