physically and emotionally, too.

287
02:06:15,037 --> 02:06:19,394
- Did she say something?
- It's...

288
02:06:19,557 --> 02:06:23,596
I just think you should
keep your distance a little.

289
02:06:26,757 --> 02:06:29,271
Mind your own business.

290
02:06:51,677 --> 02:06:54,145
Oh, my God!

291
02:07:04,997 --> 02:07:09,832
Are you all right?
I brought you some tea.

292
02:07:09,997 --> 02:07:13,785
It's herbal. Lemon verbena.
Very relaxing.

293
02:07:13,957 --> 02:07:18,906
It's almost like a drug.
I'm surprised it's legal. Here.

294
02:07:19,077 --> 02:07:23,275
- You gave us quite a scare.
- There were so many.

295
02:07:23,437 --> 02:07:26,349
It's the poison.
They go up into the rafters to die.

296
02:07:26,517 --> 02:07:31,750
It's painless, but it does
leave a lot of bodies around.

297
02:07:32,837 --> 02:07:37,353
- God!
- It's over now. You just relax.

298
02:07:39,077 --> 02:07:44,356
I feel so strange.
I don't know what's wrong with me.

299
02:07:45,957 --> 02:07:49,233
I know exactly how you feel.

300
02:07:50,397 --> 02:07:52,752
Your muscles ache.

301
02:07:52,917 --> 02:07:56,796
And your skin is so sensitive.

302
02:07:56,957 --> 02:08:02,748
And your mind...
that just goes haywire, doesn't it?

303
02:08:09,997 --> 02:08:17,153
Helen...
you are a lovely young woman.

304
02:08:17,317 --> 02:08:20,548
You just remember that...

305
02:08:20,717 --> 02:08:27,475
