02:26:47,157 --> 02:26:51,275
She's so filled with anxieties,
I don't know what to do.

474
02:26:51,437 --> 02:26:56,227
It's all those books
on pregnancy she's reading.

475
02:26:56,397 --> 02:27:00,913
She's got it in her mind
that first babies are always late.

476
02:27:01,077 --> 02:27:07,107
If she's a week or two late, it's no
problem. We can induce right here.

477
02:27:07,277 --> 02:27:11,395
Oxytocin brings on contractions
within 24 hours.

478
02:27:11,557 --> 02:27:16,790
- We use that for horses.
- Yes, it's exactly the same.

479
02:27:16,957 --> 02:27:22,236
Whatever it is, we got the cure.
It's not like it was in our day.

480
02:27:22,397 --> 02:27:25,514
Can you believe it?
Me a grandmother.

481
02:27:25,677 --> 02:27:28,635
No, I can't.

482
02:27:28,797 --> 02:27:31,834
Tell me, is it a boy or a girl?

483
02:27:31,997 --> 02:27:34,875
You'll get me into trouble.

484
02:27:35,037 --> 02:27:39,553
I just want to get the colour right.
You know I hate yellow.

485
02:27:39,717 --> 02:27:43,392
- What colour do you like?
- Well...

486
02:27:43,557 --> 02:27:47,789
Blue was lucky for me 25 years ago.

487
02:27:47,957 --> 02:27:55,033
Why don't you play your hunch then?
Bye, Martha.

488
02:28:01,277 --> 02:28:05,156
O XYTOCIN

489
02:28:14,077 --> 02:28:16,830
Don't worry. I'll be here packing.

490
02:28:16,997 --> 02:28:21,275
- Are you sure you want me to go?
- I want you to go and win.

491
02:28:21,437 --> 02:28:25,589
Then get your ass back here
as fast as you can.

492
02:28:28,277 --> 02:28:34,068
It's more than three hours away and
you want to get there before dinner.

493
02:28:36,117 --> 02:28:39,712
Come on, you lovebirds,
he's already in the van.

494
02:28:39,877 --> 02:28:43,950
Goodbye, baby. Good luck.

495
02:28:44,117 --> 02:28:47,666
You take care, both of you.
I'll be back tomorrow night.

496
02:28:50,277 --> 02:28:54,190
- Bye.
- Bye.

497
02:28:57,877 --> 02:29:03,349
It won't be long before Kilronan
is everything it ever was.

498
02:29:03,517 --> 02:29:07,032
- Kind of a shame, isn't it?
- What is?

499
02:29:07,197 --> 02:29:11,395
That we won't be here to see it.

500
02:29:51,317 --> 02:29:56,345
- Hey!
- And the same hey to you, darling.

501
02:29:57,957 --> 02:30:02,553
You're looking even lovelier.

502
02:30:02,717 --> 02:30:05,470
I've brought you something.

503
02:30:05,637 --> 02:30:11,951
Kind of a head start
on baby pictures.

504
02:30:12,117 --> 02:30:16,633
This'll be a big hit around here.
These nuns love a foetus.

505
02:30:16,797 --> 02:30:21,951
- I came to say goodbye.
- Hello and goodbye?

506
02:30:23,037 --> 02:30:28,111
- We're going back to New York.
- Good for you.

507
02:30:29,837 --> 02:30:34,831
You're well rid of that woman.
Jackson shouldn't have come back.

508
02:30:34,997 --> 02:30:37,465
That was my idea.

509
02:30:37,637 --> 02:30:42,665
I thought he had to come back
and face all the ghosts.

510
02:30:42,837 --> 02:30:47,786
He still blames himself
for his father's death.

511
02:30:47,957 --> 02:30:53,873
No, his daddy fell on a tool that
was lying at the foot of the stairs.

512
02:30:54,037 --> 02:30:58,076
One of those things they use
to pull nails out of boards.

513
02:30:58,237 --> 02:31:03,152
He landed on it just wrong
and it crushed his sternum.

514
02:31:03,317 --> 02:31:08,072
It was in all the newspapers.
Doctors commenting right and left.

515
02:31:08,237 --> 02:31:13,186
A bizarre happening.
Jackson must accept that.

516
02:31:13,357 --> 02:31:19,353
Be careful, now. When Jack told her
he was leaving, she turned demonic.

517
02:31:20,557 --> 02:31:25,073
I can see that.
She strikes me as the jealous type.

518
02:31:25,237 --> 02:31:29,628
What possible reason could she have
to be jealous of Jack?

519
02:31:31,477 --> 02:31:36,426
Didn't he ever tell you
about Robin Hayes?

520
02:31:36,597 --> 02:31:42,866
Jack and Robin? Walk me.
These old farts shock easily.

521
02:31:58,077 --> 02:32:04,630
- What?
- Oh...

522
02:32:04,797 --> 02:32:10,110
I was just remembering
when I had Jackson.

523
02:32:10,277 --> 02:32:15,146
I thought that pain
was going to rip me in half.

524
02:32:15,317 --> 02:32:17,706
How stupid of me.

525
02:32:17,877 --> 02:32:24,191
Oh, Honey... here.
Let me get you some dessert.

526
02:32:24,357 --> 02:32:29,477
- I'm tired. I'm going upstairs.
- I made it specially for you.

527
02:32:29,637 --> 02:32:32,515
It's strawberries, your favourite.

528
02:32:32,677 --> 02:32:38,627
Indulge yourself. Go on, take it.

529
02:32:38,797 --> 02:32:42,506
You deserve it.

530
02:32:44,917 --> 02:32:48,512
- I think I'll take it up to bed.
- Yes.

531
02:32:48,677 --> 02:32:53,626
Go on. That baby needs
all the rest he can get.

532
02:32:55,117 --> 02:32:56,994
Or she.

533
02:32:58,957 --> 02:33:02,188
- Or she.
- Good night, Martha.

534
02:33:02,357 --> 02:33:05,793
Sweet dreams.

535
02:33:17,397 --> 02:33:24,235
Tender around that joint.
I'll wrap it.

536
02:33:30,837 --> 02:33:36,434
My God, I am heartily sorry for
offending thee. I detest my sins.

537
02:33:36,597 --> 02:33:40,431
Most of all because
they offend thee, my God -

538
02:33:40,597 --> 02:33:44,749
- who sent me a daughter-in-law
from the land of the Moabites.

539
02:33:44,917 --> 02:33:50,275
I will go with you, she said
and your people will be my people.

540
02:33:50,437 --> 02:33:56,069
She laid on the threshing floor and
did as her mother-in-law instructed.

541
02:33:57,557 --> 02:34:00,435
<i>And she conceived a son.</i>

542
02:34:00,597 --> 02:34:06,035
<i>And God said he will be born</i>
<i>and renew your life.</i>

543
02:34:06,197 --> 02:34:12,272
<i>He is born of your daughter-in-law</i>
<i>and is better than seven sons.</i>

544
02:34:12,437 --> 02:34:16,908
<i>You understand, don't you?</i>
<i>This is for him...</i>

545
02:34:17,077 --> 02:34:23,107
<i>... and the precious baby who has</i>
<i>no one to protect him from her.</i>

546
02:34:24,237 --> 02:34:29,630
Hey, are you kicking me again?

547
02:34:29,797 --> 02:34:36,145
<i>He is weak... my son.</i>
<i>I am his strength.</i>

548
02:34:37,077 --> 02:34:39,637
Are you hungry?

549
02:34:39,797 --> 02:34:45,394
<i>And God said let the woman</i>
<i>of emptiness become full.</i>

550
02:34:45,557 --> 02:34:49,630
<i>And you who are most worthy</i> - 

551
02:34:49,797 --> 02:34:55,667
- <i>shall take the child to your</i>
<i>bosom and become its mother.</i>

552
02:34:55,837 --> 02:35:00,513
And the women neighbours
will give him a name -

553
02:35:00,677 --> 02:35:04,795
- saying, a son is born to you.

554
02:35:04,957 --> 02:35:08,029
To you.

555
02:35:10,517 --> 02:35:19,471
I firmly resolve to confess my sins,
do penance and amend my life.

556
02:35:19,637 --> 02:35:21,832
Amen.

557
02:36:54,677 --> 02:36:57,430
Martha?

558
02:37:49,317 --> 02:37:53,435
- No, no...
- Helen!

559
02:37:58,117 --> 02:38:02,110
You bad girl, you!
You found me out, didn't you?

560
02:38:04,797 --> 02:38:10,633
- I saw a light.
- Is there no stopping you?

561
02:38:10,797 --> 02:38:16,110
What is all this?
What are you doing?

562
02:38:16,277 --> 02:38:21,067
It was my surprise for you, honey.

563
02:38:21,237 --> 02:38:24,707
- Surprise?
- I set it all up like this.

564
02:38:24,877 --> 02:38:29,905
It's for you. I was going
to ship it up to you in New York.

565
02:38:33,237 --> 02:38:37,071
I just thought the presentation
would be so vivid.

566
02:38:40,557 --> 02:38:45,392
- I'm sorry.
- It's all right, honey.

567
02:38:45,557 --> 02:38:49,311
We can still show it to Jackson.

568
02:38:49,477 --> 02:38:54,392
- Won't that be fun?
- Yes.

569
02:38:54,557 --> 02:39:00,746
- Are you all right?
- I'm just tired.

570
02:39:00,917 --> 02:39:08,426
Let me take you back up to the house
to bed. You've no shoes on.

571
02:39:19,757 --> 02:39:24,706
- Wait.
- What is it? Is it the baby?

572
02:39:24,877 --> 02:39:28,426
- Could I have some water?
- We're almost at the house.

573
02:39:28,597 --> 02:39:31,316
I need some water.

574
02:39:33,557 --> 02:39:36,196
All right, I'll be right back.

575
02:40:56,157 --> 02:41:00,275
Howdy. What can I do you for today,
my pretty lady?

576
02:41:01,157 --> 02:41:03,352
<i>Pretty lady...</i>

577
02:41:03,517 --> 02:41:06,429
<i>I know where you live.</i>

578
02:41:09,037 --> 02:41:11,346
My God!

579
02:41:11,517 --> 02:41:14,156
Just trying to be friendly, darling.

580
02:41:16,917 --> 02:41:18,873
Goddamn!

581
02:42:52,277 --> 02:42:55,269
What on earth are you doing?

582
02:43:00,077 --> 02:43:04,514
Do you think you're some alley cat
dropping your litter by the road?

583
02:43:20,037 --> 02:43:23,632
The pain is terrible, isn't it?

584
02:43:23,797 --> 02:43:27,915
Darling, I can feel it myself.
I can feel what you're feeling.

585
02:43:28,077 --> 02:43:33,356
- My God, help me.
- I wish I could.

586
02:43:33,517 --> 02:43:37,396
Believe me, I wish I could
give you something...

587
02:43:37,557 --> 02:43:40,788
...but I can't.

588
02:43:40,957 --> 02:43:44,552
You just have to go through it...

589
02:43:44,717 --> 02:43:49,029
...and feel it deeply.

590
02:43:49,197 --> 02:43:55,875
Then you will never forget
what your child means to you.

591
02:44:03,357 --> 02:44:05,473
I'm begging you.

592
02:44:09,717 --> 02:44:12,675
Well...

593
02:44:27,037 --> 02:44:32,236
This is the big one, isn't it?
I've put a couple of C-notes on him.

594
02:44:32,397 --> 02:44:35,833
I sent a buyer up to Kilronan
the other day.

595
02:44:35,997 --> 02:44:38,636
Martha told him you were staying.

596
02:44:38,797 --> 02:44:42,836
She did?

597
02:44:44,077 --> 02:44:49,310
It's almost over. Breathe, darling.

598
02:44:49,477 --> 02:44:54,392
It's okay, you're all right.
Breathe, Helen.

599
02:44:59,357 --> 02:45:03,270
Hello?
Jackson, I was hoping it was you.

600
02:45:06,277 --> 02:45:11,226
- Of course everything's all right.
- Can I talk to her?

601
02:45:11,397 --> 02:45:14,594
She's right here, just a minute.

602
02:45:14,837 --> 02:45:19,547
- <i>How did the morning workout go?</i>
- Jackson!

603
02:45:19,717 --> 02:45:23,392
- Great. He's running well.
- Did you draw your post position?

604
02:45:23,557 --> 02:45:28,187
Yes. Can I please talk to Helen?

605
02:45:28,477 --> 02:45:33,949
Jackson, I'm losing you.
I can't hear you any more.

606
02:45:48,077 --> 02:45:53,390
You're doing good.
Push a little bit harder. Push!

607
02:45:53,557 --> 02:45:57,596
- Push!
- I am pushing, you bitch!

608
02:45:57,757 --> 02:46:02,751
They're at the post.
The flag is up.

609
02:46:05,717 --> 02:46:10,188
One last time. Push down.
Push, Helen, push!

610
02:46:10,357 --> 02:46:16,512
You can do it. Come on, push.

611
02:46:16,677 --> 02:46:20,909
I can see it. Oh, my God!

612
02:46:21,077 --> 02:46:25,275
It's coming. Push, Helen.

613
02:46:32,357 --> 02:46:34,917
Yes...

614
02:46:40,757 --> 02:46:46,354
Push, Helen. Don't you quit now.

615
02:46:46,517 --> 02:46:52,035
My God! It's a beautiful little boy.

616
02:46:53,197 --> 02:46:56,633
He looks just like Jackson.

617
02:47:01,037 --> 02:47:05,030
- What a beautiful boy.
- Give him to me.

618
02:47:05,197 --> 02:47:09,190
Mama's going to get you
all cleaned up.

619
02:47:10,437 --> 02:47:13,349
No, Martha, give me my baby!

620
02:47:13,517 --> 02:47:16,793
I'll love you, dear.

621
02:47:16,957 --> 02:47:20,791
I'll love you
till China and Africa meet...

622
02:47:20,957 --> 02:47:25,906
...and the river jumps over
the mountains.

623
02:47:34,877 --> 02:47:38,836
Helen, you're losing so much blood.

624
02:47:38,997 --> 02:47:42,433
Look at the mess you've made
of my linens.

625
02:47:48,117 --> 02:47:52,508
I really wanted us
to be a family together.

626
02:47:52,677 --> 02:47:57,546
Really I did... but I don't know
if that's possible any more.

627
02:48:00,357 --> 02:48:08,913
It's a pity... but you were so weak
during your pregnancy.

628
02:48:09,077 --> 02:48:14,595
And you would insist on having
that baby right here at home.

629
02:48:16,197 --> 02:48:18,950
I did my best, you know I did.

630
02:48:20,917 --> 02:48:24,671
Of course, you won't remember it
that way, will you?

631
02:48:24,837 --> 02:48:29,865
You'll tell them all sorts of things
about me. Make up stories.

632
02:48:36,877 --> 02:48:39,266
MORPHINE

633
02:48:39,437 --> 02:48:43,589
It's dangerous to take
more than just a drop of this.

634
02:48:46,677 --> 02:48:51,114
Jackson and I will raise that baby
the way he deserves.

635
02:48:52,797 --> 02:48:54,469
I'm home.

636
02:48:54,637 --> 02:48:58,391
You'd have been proud.

637
02:49:04,277 --> 02:49:08,156
Mom.

638
02:49:09,517 --> 02:49:11,906
I'll be right there.

639
02:49:14,717 --> 02:49:18,505
Helen...
I've been calling and calling.

640
02:49:25,357 --> 02:49:27,427
It's a boy.

641
02:49:27,597 --> 02:49:33,308
He came so fast.
I had no time to call anybody.

642
02:49:33,477 --> 02:49:38,267
Your wife was so brave and
so strong. She needs to sleep now.

643
02:49:38,437 --> 02:49:42,988
You have no idea
what she's been through today.

644
02:49:43,157 --> 02:49:46,786
- Don't you want to hold your son?
- Is she okay?

645
02:49:46,957 --> 02:49:49,391
Helen's doing just great.

646
02:49:49,557 --> 02:49:55,154
You come with me. We've got to give
this baby boy his first bath.

647
02:49:57,317 --> 02:50:02,027
She's fine. She just needs to sleep.

648
02:50:47,317 --> 02:50:50,514
Hey, Mom.

649
02:50:50,677 --> 02:50:57,355
You can't sleep in this chair.
Go to bed. I'll keep watch.

650
02:50:57,517 --> 02:51:02,386
Thanks, Mom... not a chance.
I want to be here when she wakes up.

651
02:51:02,557 --> 02:51:07,108
I wouldn't miss it for the world.
I don't care about kinks in my neck.

652
02:51:07,277 --> 02:51:12,146
Your wife and baby are going
to need you at full strength.

653
02:51:12,317 --> 02:51:16,356
- Thank for seeing her through this.
- To bed now.

654
02:51:16,517 --> 02:51:21,511
March.
I won't take no for an answer.

655
02:51:21,677 --> 02:51:24,555
Shut up, Mom.
Quit while you're ahead.

656
02:51:27,597 --> 02:51:30,316
Good night.

657
02:51:58,157 --> 02:52:00,625
Hi, Mommy.

658
02:52:01,677 --> 02:52:05,192
Want to meet your little baby boy?

659
02:52:12,757 --> 02:52:15,396
This is your mommy.

660
02:52:26,357 --> 02:52:29,986
- How are you feeling?
- Okay.

661
02:52:31,557 --> 02:52:35,948
- Where's Martha?
- I think she's asleep.

662
02:52:36,117 --> 02:52:40,030
She said you really went through it.

663
02:52:40,197 --> 02:52:46,147
- Thank God she was here.
- Yeah.

664
02:52:46,317 --> 02:52:49,195
Honey, will you do me a favour?

665
02:52:49,357 --> 02:52:54,989
- Ask her to make us some breakfast.
- You're hungry... that's good.

666
02:53:01,877 --> 02:53:06,109
If you need anything,
I'll be downstairs.

667
02:53:22,197 --> 02:53:24,836
There you are... Daddy.

668
02:53:26,957 --> 02:53:30,791
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

669
02:53:30,957 --> 02:53:34,666
- You've been outside.
- I was looking for something.

670
02:53:36,237 --> 02:53:44,155
- You really ought to be in bed.
- I feel wonderful, Martha.

671
02:53:44,317 --> 02:53:49,471
I slept so deeply. It's like
I was drugged or something.

672
02:53:49,637 --> 02:53:53,346
- It's like 20 years passed.
- It has.

673
02:53:53,517 --> 02:53:57,305
- We just forgot to tell you.
- Great.

674
02:53:57,477 --> 02:54:03,074
- What's in the bag?
- This thing I found in the barn.

675
02:54:04,077 --> 02:54:07,114
Those eggs smell good.

676
02:54:10,397 --> 02:54:14,709
- What?
- What yourself. What's the mystery?

677
02:54:14,877 --> 02:54:20,076
This is such a happy day. I don't
want to bring everybody down.

678
02:54:20,237 --> 02:54:25,391
Come on, Baby, don't keep us all
in suspense. What's in the bag?

679
02:54:25,637 --> 02:54:29,312
It's one of those things
that killed Jackson's daddy.

680
02:54:29,477 --> 02:54:35,029
- I'd never seen one before.
- What are you talking about?

681
02:54:35,197 --> 02:54:38,826
Jackson has a son of his own now.

682
02:54:38,997 --> 02:54:42,467
He's got to let go
of all those old ghosts.

683
02:54:42,637 --> 02:54:46,471
I had to find one of these things.

684
02:54:46,637 --> 02:54:52,507
Now I'll bury it in the ground,
so it never harms this family again.

685
02:54:52,677 --> 02:54:58,070
- I know that sounds hormonal...
- My father fell down the stairs.

686
02:54:58,237 --> 02:55:01,195
It wasn't the fall that killed him.

687
02:55:01,357 --> 02:55:07,432
Downstairs, your mama found
that he had fallen on this thing.

688
02:55:07,597 --> 02:55:12,796
It was a freak accident.
It was even in the newspapers.

689
02:55:12,957 --> 02:55:17,587
He fell on something
at the bottom of the stairs?

690
02:55:17,757 --> 02:55:22,911
Helen's right, this is not the day
we should be talking about this.

691
02:55:23,077 --> 02:55:26,035
Yeah, he fell. He fell on this.

692
02:55:29,157 --> 02:55:33,947
There must be lots of these
laying round a place like this.

693
02:55:34,117 --> 02:55:39,987
- What are you doing?
- Whatever do you mean?

694
02:55:40,157 --> 02:55:46,312
That's how Jack died. He fell
with inconceivable precision.

695
02:55:46,477 --> 02:55:51,915
This tool killed him as surely as if
it had been smashed into his body.

696
02:55:54,677 --> 02:55:59,353
- You were working on that shed.
- How could you remember that?

697
02:55:59,517 --> 02:56:01,667
You were only seven.

698
02:56:01,837 --> 02:56:05,512
I remember particularly you
holding that when you hugged me.

699
02:56:05,677 --> 02:56:11,673
When you dropped it, it made
this really loud clanging sound.

700
02:56:13,557 --> 02:56:19,109
Why are you doing this?
Trying to tear my family apart.

701
02:56:19,277 --> 02:56:22,553
- You lost your own parents...
- Mom, she wasn't...

702
02:56:22,717 --> 02:56:27,313
She's not fooling anybody.
Do you know what she's implying?

703
02:56:27,477 --> 02:56:33,393
If I did hold one of those things,
it wasn't the only one we had.

704
02:56:33,557 --> 02:56:39,348
You remember that day.
You remember the fall.

705
02:56:39,517 --> 02:56:43,476
That fall
could have killed anybody who...

706
02:56:43,637 --> 02:56:49,587
Martha! No one's implying
that you killed Jack!

707
02:56:49,757 --> 02:56:55,195
Lots of wives have affairs
and don't kill their husbands.

708
02:56:55,357 --> 02:56:59,350
- My father was having the affair.
- No, he wasn't.

709
02:56:59,517 --> 02:57:05,114
Robin Hayes was a wrangler that
Martha was having an affair with.

710
02:57:05,277 --> 02:57:08,826
Alice told you that, did she?

711
02:57:08,997 --> 02:57:12,546
That's just the kind of twisted lie
Alice would invent.

712
02:57:12,717 --> 02:57:17,029
Now your wife's trying
to use it against me.

713
02:57:18,797 --> 02:57:22,028
I just talked to Robin Hayes
half an hour ago.

714
02:57:22,197 --> 02:57:26,475
- Would you like to speak to him?
- No!

715
02:57:27,157 --> 02:57:32,106
Robin Hayes died last year of a
heart attack, one you didn't cause.

716
02:57:33,517 --> 02:57:39,956
You just couldn't bear to let
a happy family be, could you?

717
02:57:40,957 --> 02:57:45,633
We were so close
to being happy, Jackson.

718
02:57:45,797 --> 02:57:49,028
Here's how close we were.

719
02:57:51,717 --> 02:57:56,586
- She tried to kill me last night.
- That's a lie.

720
02:57:56,757 --> 02:58:01,990
Your father was leaving.
That's why she killed him.

721
02:58:02,157 --> 02:58:05,115
She made you think that you did it -

722
02:58:05,277 --> 02:58:09,270
- so that she could bind you to her
for the rest of your life.

723
02:58:09,437 --> 02:58:13,828
I want you to throw this lying bitch
out of my house.

724
02:58:13,997 --> 02:58:16,989
Yeah, there's already one of those.

725
02:58:17,157 --> 02:58:20,832
- You'll never prove anything.
- She doesn't have to.

726
02:58:24,037 --> 02:58:27,074
- Jackson, you can't...
- Shut up!

727
02:58:29,517 --> 02:58:32,077
Everything about you is a lie.

728
02:58:32,237 --> 02:58:36,628
This place and everything in it
will be sold.

729
02:58:36,797 --> 02:58:41,029
You will never see me
or any member of my family again.

730
02:58:43,357 --> 02:58:46,315
But I did it all for you.

731
02:58:46,477 --> 02:58:49,708
You are not my mother.

732
02:58:57,397 --> 02:59:01,151
You did this. You tricked him.

733
02:59:01,317 --> 02:59:05,754
You got yourself pregnant.
I know what you're after.

734
02:59:05,917 --> 02:59:12,356
You want my farm, my land, my boy!

735
02:59:12,917 --> 02:59:18,594
You want to take everything I have.
Don't you see what she's doing?

736
02:59:20,837 --> 02:59:23,795
She wants to be me.

737
02:59:34,517 --> 02:59:36,747
So long, Martha.

738
03:00:18,957 --> 03:00:22,267
Grandma.

